classes.name: EconomyResponse
classes.comment:
Indicates a typical Return for an Economy method.  
 It includes a {@link ResponseType} indicating whether the plugin currently being used for Economy actually allows
 the method, or if the operation was a success or failure.

fields.name: type
fields.comment:
Success or failure of call. Using Enum of ResponseType to determine valid
 outcomes

fields.name: errorMessage
fields.comment: Error message if the variable 'type' is ResponseType.FAILURE

methods.name: transactionSuccess
methods.comment: Checks if an operation was successful

classes.name: EconomyResponse.ResponseType
classes.comment: Enum for types of Responses indicating the status of a method call.

methods.name: isEnabled
methods.comment: Checks if economy method is enabled.

methods.name: getName
methods.comment: Gets name of economy method

methods.name: hasBankSupport
methods.comment: Returns true if the given implementation supports banks.

methods.name: fractionalDigits
methods.comment:
Some economy plugins round off after a certain number of digits.
 This function returns the number of digits the plugin keeps
 or -1 if no rounding occurs.

methods.name: format
methods.comment:
Format amount into a human readable String This provides translation into
 economy specific formatting to improve consistency between plugins.

methods.name: currencyNamePlural
methods.comment:
Returns the name of the currency in plural form.
 If the economy being used does not support currency names then an empty string will be returned.

methods.name: currencyNameSingular
methods.comment:
Returns the name of the currency in singular form.
 If the economy being used does not support currency names then an empty string will be returned.

methods.name: hasAccount
methods.comment:
Checks if this player has an account on the server yet
 This will always return true if the player has joined the server at least once
 as all major economy plugins auto-generate a player account when the player joins the server

methods.name: hasAccount
methods.comment:
Checks if this player has an account on the server yet on the given world
 This will always return true if the player has joined the server at least once
 as all major economy plugins auto-generate a player account when the player joins the server

methods.name: getBalance
methods.comment: Gets balance of a player

methods.name: getBalance
methods.comment:
Gets balance of a player on the specified world.
 IMPLEMENTATION SPECIFIC - if an economy plugin does not support this the global balance will be returned.

methods.name: has
methods.comment: Checks if the player account has the amount - DO NOT USE NEGATIVE AMOUNTS

methods.name: has
methods.comment:
Checks if the player account has the amount in a given world - DO NOT USE NEGATIVE AMOUNTS
 IMPLEMENTATION SPECIFIC - if an economy plugin does not support this the global balance will be returned.

methods.name: withdrawPlayer
methods.comment: Withdraw an amount from a player - DO NOT USE NEGATIVE AMOUNTS

methods.name: withdrawPlayer
methods.comment:
Withdraw an amount from a player on a given world - DO NOT USE NEGATIVE AMOUNTS
 IMPLEMENTATION SPECIFIC - if an economy plugin does not support this the global balance will be returned.

methods.name: depositPlayer
methods.comment: Deposit an amount to a player - DO NOT USE NEGATIVE AMOUNTS

methods.name: depositPlayer
methods.comment:
Deposit an amount to a player - DO NOT USE NEGATIVE AMOUNTS
 IMPLEMENTATION SPECIFIC - if an economy plugin does not support this the global balance will be returned.

methods.name: createBank
methods.comment: Creates a bank account with the specified name and the player as the owner

methods.name: deleteBank
methods.comment: Deletes a bank account with the specified name.

methods.name: bankBalance
methods.comment: Returns the amount the bank has

methods.name: bankHas
methods.comment: Returns true or false whether the bank has the amount specified - DO NOT USE NEGATIVE AMOUNTS

methods.name: bankWithdraw
methods.comment: Withdraw an amount from a bank account - DO NOT USE NEGATIVE AMOUNTS

methods.name: bankDeposit
methods.comment: Deposit an amount into a bank account - DO NOT USE NEGATIVE AMOUNTS

methods.name: isBankOwner
methods.comment: Check if a player is the owner of a bank account

methods.name: isBankMember
methods.comment: Check if the player is a member of the bank account

methods.name: getBanks
methods.comment: Gets the list of banks

methods.name: createPlayerAccount
methods.comment: Attempts to create a player account for the given player

methods.name: createPlayerAccount
methods.comment:
Attempts to create a player account for the given player on the specified world
 IMPLEMENTATION SPECIFIC - if an economy plugin does not support this then false will always be returned.

classes.name: Permission
classes.comment: The main Permission API - allows for group and player based permission tests

methods.name: getName
methods.comment: Gets name of permission method

methods.name: isEnabled
methods.comment: Checks if permission method is enabled.

methods.name: hasSuperPermsCompat
methods.comment: Returns if the permission system is or attempts to be compatible with super-perms.

methods.name: has
methods.comment:
Checks if a CommandSender has a permission node.
 This will return the result of bukkits, generic .hasPermission() method and is identical in all cases.
 This method will explicitly fail if the registered permission system does not register permissions in bukkit.
 
 For easy checking of a commandsender

methods.name: has
methods.comment: Checks if player has a permission node. (Short for playerHas(...)

methods.name: playerHas
methods.comment:
Checks if player has a permission node.
 Supports NULL value for World if the permission system registered supports global permissions.
 But May return odd values if the servers registered permission system does not have a global permission store.

methods.name: playerHas
methods.comment:
Checks if player has a permission node.
 Defaults to world-specific permission check if the permission system supports it.
 See {@link #playerHas(String, OfflinePlayer, String)} for explicit global or world checks.

methods.name: playerAdd
methods.comment:
Add permission to a player.
 Supports NULL value for World if the permission system registered supports global permissions.
 But May return odd values if the servers registered permission system does not have a global permission store.

methods.name: playerAdd
methods.comment:
Add permission to a player ONLY for the world the player is currently on.
 This is a world-specific operation, if you want to add global permission you must explicitly use NULL for the world.
 See {@link #playerAdd(String, OfflinePlayer, String)} for global permission use.

methods.name: playerAddTransient
methods.comment:
Add transient permission to a player.
 This implementation can be used by any subclass which implements a "pure" superperms plugin, i.e. 
 one that only needs the built-in Bukkit API to add transient permissions to a player.

methods.name: playerAddTransient
methods.comment:
Add transient permission to a player.
 This operation adds a permission onto the player object in bukkit via Bukkit's permission interface.

methods.name: playerAddTransient
methods.comment:
Adds a world specific transient permission to the player, may only work with some permission managers.
 Defaults to GLOBAL permissions for any permission system that does not support world-specific transient permissions!

methods.name: playerAddTransient
methods.comment:
Adds a world specific transient permission to the player, may only work with some permission managers.
 Defaults to GLOBAL permissions for any permission system that does not support world-specific transient permissions!

methods.name: playerRemoveTransient
methods.comment:
Removes a world specific transient permission from the player, may only work with some permission managers.
 Defaults to GLOBAL permissions for any permission system that does not support world-specific transient permissions!

methods.name: playerRemoveTransient
methods.comment:
Removes a world specific transient permission from the player, may only work with some permission managers.
 Defaults to GLOBAL permissions for any permission system that does not support world-specific transient permissions!

methods.name: playerRemove
methods.comment:
Remove permission from a player.
 Supports NULL value for World if the permission system registered supports global permissions.
 But May return odd values if the servers registered permission system does not have a global permission store.

methods.name: playerRemove
methods.comment:
Remove permission from a player.
 Supports NULL value for World if the permission system registered supports global permissions.
 But May return odd values if the servers registered permission system does not have a global permission store.

methods.name: playerRemove
methods.comment:
Remove permission from a player.
 Will attempt to remove permission from the player on the player's current world.  This is NOT a global operation.

methods.name: playerRemoveTransient
methods.comment:
Remove transient permission from a player.
 This implementation can be used by any subclass which implements a "pure" superperms plugin, i.e. 
 one that only needs the built-in Bukkit API to remove transient permissions from a player.  Any subclass
 implementing a plugin which provides its own API for this needs to override this method.

methods.name: playerRemoveTransient
methods.comment: Remove transient permission from a player.

methods.name: groupHas
methods.comment:
Checks if group has a permission node.
 Supports NULL value for World if the permission system registered supports global permissions.
 But May return odd values if the servers registered permission system does not have a global permission store.

methods.name: groupHas
methods.comment:
Checks if group has a permission node.
 Supports NULL value for World if the permission system registered supports global permissions.
 But May return odd values if the servers registered permission system does not have a global permission store.

methods.name: groupAdd
methods.comment:
Add permission to a group.
 Supports NULL value for World if the permission system registered supports global permissions.
 But May return odd values if the servers registered permission system does not have a global permission store.

methods.name: groupAdd
methods.comment:
Add permission to a group.
 Supports NULL value for World if the permission system registered supports global permissions.
 But May return odd values if the servers registered permission system does not have a global permission store.

methods.name: groupRemove
methods.comment:
Remove permission from a group.
 Supports NULL value for World if the permission system registered supports global permissions.
 But May return odd values if the servers registered permission system does not have a global permission store.

methods.name: groupRemove
methods.comment:
Remove permission from a group.
 Supports NULL value for World if the permission system registered supports global permissions.
 But May return odd values if the servers registered permission system does not have a global permission store.

methods.name: playerInGroup
methods.comment:
Check if player is member of a group.
 Supports NULL value for World if the permission system registered supports global permissions.
 But May return odd values if the servers registered permission system does not have a global permission store.

methods.name: playerInGroup
methods.comment:
Check if player is member of a group.
 This method will ONLY check groups for which the player is in that are defined for the current world.
 This may result in odd return behaviour depending on what permission system has been registered.

methods.name: playerAddGroup
methods.comment:
Add player to a group.
 Supports NULL value for World if the permission system registered supports global permissions.
 But May return odd values if the servers registered permission system does not have a global permission store.

methods.name: playerAddGroup
methods.comment:
Add player to a group.
 This will add a player to the group on the current World.  This may return odd results if the permission system
 being used on the server does not support world-specific groups, or if the group being added to is a global group.

methods.name: playerRemoveGroup
methods.comment:
Remove player from a group.
 Supports NULL value for World if the permission system registered supports global permissions.
 But May return odd values if the servers registered permission system does not have a global permission store.

methods.name: playerRemoveGroup
methods.comment:
Remove player from a group.
 This will add a player to the group on the current World.  This may return odd results if the permission system
 being used on the server does not support world-specific groups, or if the group being added to is a global group.

methods.name: getPlayerGroups
methods.comment:
Gets the list of groups that this player has
 Supports NULL value for World if the permission system registered supports global permissions.
 But May return odd values if the servers registered permission system does not have a global permission store.

methods.name: getPlayerGroups
methods.comment:
Returns a list of world-specific groups that this player is currently in. May return unexpected results if
 you are looking for global groups, or if the registered permission system does not support world-specific groups.
 See {@link #getPlayerGroups(String, OfflinePlayer)} for better control of World-specific or global groups.

methods.name: getPrimaryGroup
methods.comment:
Gets players primary group
 Supports NULL value for World if the permission system registered supports global permissions.
 But May return odd values if the servers registered permission system does not have a global permission store.

methods.name: getPrimaryGroup
methods.comment:
Get players primary group.
 Defaults to the players current world, so may return only world-specific groups.
 In most cases {@link #getPrimaryGroup(String, OfflinePlayer)} is preferable.

methods.name: getGroups
methods.comment: Returns a list of all known groups

methods.name: hasGroupSupport
methods.comment: Returns true if the given implementation supports groups.
